In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 11, 2015, as General Pulaski Memorial Day. The day is meant to honor the legacy of Brigadier General Casimir Pulaski, a Polish-born hero of the American Revolutionary War who sacrificed his life for the United States. Pulaski fought for the ideals of liberty and self-determination and played a role in shaping the strong relationship between Poland and the United States. He served in the Continental Army and saved the life of General George Washington. Pulaski's bravery and leadership exemplify the commitment of men and women to a cause greater than themselves. On this day, the President encourages Americans to commemorate Pulaski's sacrifice and honor all those who defend the freedom of the nation.